Vintage-style illustration of two elegant glass bottles connected by an ornate copper pipe system, one bottle filled with swirling angular brackets and nested tree-like structures in deep blue ink, the other containing curly braces and colon-separated pairs in warm amber. The liquids appear to be slowly transforming as they flow through the connecting tubes, with small bubbles rising. The scene is set on a worn wooden apothecary table with aged brass fittings and Victorian scientific instruments scattered around. Sepia-toned with rich patina, evoking 19th-century chemistry laboratories and the art of transmutation.
